              NEWS & NEWSWORTHY 






















                          May 3, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Reports First Quarter Earnings

Compass Minerals reported first-quarter net earnings of $21.5 million, or $0.63 per diluted share, compared to $49.7 million, or $1.46 per diluted share, in the first quarter of 2016.














                          April 25, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Announces Departure of Chief Financial Officer

Compass Minerals announced today that effective immediately its chief financial officer, Patrick “Doug” Linehan, is departing the company due to unforeseen personal circumstances. Linehan’s departure involves no disputes with the company or issues regarding accounting practices, financial statements or operations.














                          April 12, 2017                        


Diana Toman Named to Ingram’s 2017 Class of 40 Under Forty

Diana Toman, senior vice president, general counsel and corporate secretary, was named to Ingram’s 2017 Class of 40 Under Forty. Each year, this award program recognizes 40 up-and-coming business and civic leaders in the Kansas City region.














                          March 28, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Names Patrick D. Linehan Chief Financial Officer

Compass Minerals today announced the appointment of Patrick “Doug” Linehan as the company’s chief financial officer effective April 3, 2017.














                          March 23, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Ratifies Three-Year Agreement with  Employees at Unity Plant

Compass Minerals has reached a three-year agreement with Unity plant employees represented by Unifor Local 677.














                          March 21, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Issues 2016 Annual Report

Compass Minerals released its 2016 Annual Report today. 














                          March 9, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Celebrates International Women’s Day

Compass Minerals marked International Women’s Day with its second annual celebration, broadcasted from the company’s headquarters.














                          February 8, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Reports Solid Fourth-Quarter Earnings Boosted by Brazilian Acquisition

Compass Minerals posted solid fourth-quarter and full-year 2016 earnings driven by the resilient performance of the salt business and the contribution of the Brazilian specialty plant nutrition company, Produquímica, which was acquired on October 3, 2016.














                          February 3, 2017                        


Winsford Site Plants 1,400 Trees with Cheshire Wildlife Trust

In one week, the Winsford site, along with the Cheshire Wildlife Trust, planted 1,400 trees around the site.














                          February 2, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Increases Dividend for 14th Consecutive Year

The Board of Directors of Compass Minerals approved a 3.6 percent increase in the quarterly dividend for 2017 to $0.72 per share. This increase is effective with the company’s dividend payable March 15, 2017, to shareholders of record as of the close of business on March 1, 2017.














                          February 2, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Adds Latin American Experience to Board of Directors with Appointment of Valdemar L. Fischer

Valdemar L. Fischer has been elected to the Board of Directors of Compass Minerals. 














                          January 26, 2017                        


Compass Minerals Supports Utah Food Bank for Ninth Consecutive Year

In December, volunteers from Compass Minerals’ Ogden site delivered and assembled food baskets for Ogden’s Catholic Community Services (CCS) Joyce Hansen Hall Food Bank. More than 20 Compass Minerals volunteers unloaded the $28,000 worth of goods and assembled baskets for more than 1,600 Utah families.














